&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SALARY: &lt;/strong&gt;Reference to Agenda for Change, Band 6-7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;                  Band 6 - £31,365 – 37,890&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;                  Band 7 - £38,890 – 44,503&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOURS:  &lt;/strong&gt;1 Full time position (37.5 hours)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASE:     &lt;/strong&gt;Primary Care Networks in Nottingham North and East&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONTRACT:  &lt;/strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CLOSING DATE: &lt;/strong&gt;8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INTERVIEW DATE TO BE ASSIGNED.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PICS is the employer for this role. PICS is a local company wholly owned by GPs, specialising in community-based care, and run for the benefit of patients. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic Dietician to join our dynamic team. This permanent position is well suited to an individual who is enthusiastic about providing high quality dietetic care and supporting the educational needs of healthcare professionals, working closely with Care Homes and community teams in the PCN.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be split between practices within &lt;strong&gt;Arnold and Calverton PCN&lt;/strong&gt; - The Calverton Practice, Highcroft Surgery and Stenhouse Medical Centre - and &lt;strong&gt;Byron PCN &lt;/strong&gt;- Oakenhall Medical Centre, The OM Surgery, Torkard Hill Medical Centre, Whyburn Medical Practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work closely with multi-disciplinary teams, healthcare professionals and Care Homes, to implement and evaluate nutritional pathways for patients of the PCN.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing specialist nutritional assessment, advice and product prescribing/de-prescribing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing dietetic support to care home residents and training to staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting learning and education of healthcare professionals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting practices in the prescribing and monitoring of all nutritional products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor of Science degree in Nutrition &amp; Dietetics or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Membership with the Health and Care Professionals Council (HCPC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills with the ability to prepare and produce reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in all Microsoft programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good analytics skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A more exhaustive list of job responsibilities and necessary skills, experience and qualifications can be found in our Job Description and Person Specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BENEFITS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Auto Enrolment to the NHS Pension Scheme or an alternative government based scheme (based on eligibility)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attractive salaries (dependent on experience and qualifications) – referenced to Agenda for Change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to NHS IT systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave entitlement references Agenda for Change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On Appointment – 27 days plus 8 days bank holiday entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;After 5 years’ – 29 days plus 8 days bank holiday entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;After 10 years’ – 33 days plus 8 days bank holiday entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recognition of previous NHS service for Annual leave and sickness pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High staff satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You can contact PICS HR at pics.picshr@nhs.net for an informal discussion or with any queries. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TERMS AND CONDITIONS                            &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All applications are to be made via NHS Jobs - CVs will not be accepted. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Please note that applications received after the closing date will not normally be considered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applicants who have not heard from us with seven days of the closing date can assume that they have not been successful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;By submitting an application you consent to your personal data being shared for the purposes of recruitment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Whilst membership of the Health and Care Professionals Council (HCPC) is desirable, we will consider applications from other suitably qualified applicants, who do not hold membership&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
